bands.name: DoomFolk StarterKit
bands.bio: DoomFolk StarterKit is the songwriting project of Portland, OR based David Swick. When DoomFolk StarterKit began, Swick would write and record a song on his iPhone in one hour and then release it on Bandcamp, no matter what the end result, as an exercise in trusting instincts and eliminating self editing tendencies.

bands.name: Brian David Smith
bands.bio: Brian Smith's songwriting follows in this tradition of irreverent overextension. This approach would normally result in a tedious album if not for two things: the outrageous specificity of Brian's lyrics, and his impish urge to juxtapose unfussy, tear-in-your-beer balladry with decidedly un-country influences. The result is an album that encompasses anger, joy, disgust, bagpipes, ring modulation and balkan bichronality, all with a coherent character at the center, engaging in good faith with the phoniness of country like all the other loveable losers and no account boozers before him.
